snippet.textDisplay: So I've enjoyed your content for a while now, and as your fame and market share rose, I expected there would be bigger names appearing as sponsors as things progressed. But honestly I'm disappointed with this episode. It's 2020, and we've never been more crushingly aware of just how bad things have gotten with our planet and the ecological horrors we've set into motion over a couple generations. To see you pitch something as egregiously wasteful, unnecessary, and consumerist as these paper towels hurts man. I really expected more of you, we've all heard about the heart, the hurt, we've gotten swept up in the backstory we could identify with and love and support. I understand working to build on this wonderful thing you've worked so hard on, and that there are some tough choices to make to balance goals and values, and I can't judge that, but I think you went the wrong way on this one. I always imagined you'd champion things like reusable products and being more conscientious; being conscientious and self aware is a big part of what makes you a special brand, if you asked me, maybe others as well. Maybe that's why your subconscious made a "Spidey" slip out, and have you leave it in the final cut: because deep down you know this is the kind of ethical struggle Spidey would've chosen differently on. I don't want to support sell-out content, we've got emaciated polar bears and burning continents and all kinds of ecological terror bearing down on us and I see you throwing these giant wasteful paper towels around like that? Please make some better choices going forward.
snippet.textOriginal: So I've enjoyed your content for a while now, and as your fame and market share rose, I expected there would be bigger names appearing as sponsors as things progressed. But honestly I'm disappointed with this episode. It's 2020, and we've never been more crushingly aware of just how bad things have gotten with our planet and the ecological horrors we've set into motion over a couple generations. To see you pitch something as egregiously wasteful, unnecessary, and consumerist as these paper towels hurts man. I really expected more of you, we've all heard about the heart, the hurt, we've gotten swept up in the backstory we could identify with and love and support. I understand working to build on this wonderful thing you've worked so hard on, and that there are some tough choices to make to balance goals and values, and I can't judge that, but I think you went the wrong way on this one. I always imagined you'd champion things like reusable products and being more conscientious; being conscientious and self aware is a big part of what makes you a special brand, if you asked me, maybe others as well. Maybe that's why your subconscious made a "Spidey" slip out, and have you leave it in the final cut: because deep down you know this is the kind of ethical struggle Spidey would've chosen differently on. I don't want to support sell-out content, we've got emaciated polar bears and burning continents and all kinds of ecological terror bearing down on us and I see you throwing these giant wasteful paper towels around like that? Please make some better choices going forward.
